!!!
    if ‚Äî brief description
    Purpose:
        Conditionally executes one or more blocks of commands depending on whether the given expression evaluates to true or false.Allows for writing unambiguous branching with the option for multiple alternatives (elseif) and a default branch (else).
    Characteristics:
        - Syntax:
            if <condition> then
                ...commands...
            elseif <anotherCondition> then
                ...commands...
            else
                ...commands...
            end
        - <condition> is any expression returning boolean (true/false) ‚Äî it can include:
            - relational operators (==, !=, <, >, <=, >=, like)
            - logical operators (and, or, not)
            - parentheses to indicate precedence
         - The elseif and else branches are optional.
         - Executes from top to bottom: executes the first branch whose condition is true and skips the rest.
         - Conditions have access to all variables in the current context (keep, it, etc.).
!!!

